#: ../../../security/tpm/tpm_ftpm_tee.rst:3
msgid "Firmware TPM Driver"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/tpm/tpm_ftpm_tee.rst:5
msgid ""
"This document describes the firmware Trusted Platform Module (fTPM) device "
"driver."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/tpm/tpm_ftpm_tee.rst:9
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/tpm/tpm_ftpm_tee.rst:11
msgid ""
"This driver is a shim for firmware implemented in ARM's TrustZone "
"environment. The driver allows programs to interact with the TPM in the same "
"way they would interact with a hardware TPM."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/tpm/tpm_ftpm_tee.rst:16
msgid "Design"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/tpm/tpm_ftpm_tee.rst:18
msgid ""
"The driver acts as a thin layer that passes commands to and from a TPM "
"implemented in firmware. The driver itself doesn't contain much logic and is "
"used more like a dumb pipe between firmware and kernel/userspace."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/tpm/tpm_ftpm_tee.rst:22
msgid ""
"The firmware itself is based on the following paper: https://www.microsoft."
"com/en-us/research/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/ftpm1.pdf"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../security/tpm/tpm_ftpm_tee.rst:25
msgid ""
"When the driver is loaded it will expose ``/dev/tpmX`` character devices to "
"userspace which will enable userspace to communicate with the firmware TPM "
"through this device."
msgstr ""
